Package moulton.scalable.containers

Class PartitionPanel

java.lang.Object
moulton.scalable.utils.MenuComponent
moulton.scalable.containers.Panel
moulton.scalable.containers.PartitionPanel
public class PartitionPanel
extends Panel
PartitionPanel is a type of Panel with up to two partitions dividing up the space into four sectors: left, right, bottom, and top. Components need to be added to their sector manually using setLeft(MenuComponent), setRight(MenuComponent), setTop(MenuComponent), and setBottom(MenuComponent). The partitions can be set using setVerticalPartition(String) and setHorizontalPartition(String).
Author:
Matthew Moulton

    • topLeftCorner

      protected java.lang.Boolean topLeftCorner
      Determines how the corner is filled. If this is null and the horizontal component is set but the vertical component is not, then the horizontal component will take the corner as well. If both horizontal and vertical components are set but this is not, then the corner will be empty. If both the horizontal and vertical components are set, and this is not null, it will determine which component takes the corner (true is horizontal, false is vertical). Finally, if the horizontal component is set, the vertical component is not, but this is set to true, then the corner will be empty.
      See Also:
      setTopLeftCorner(Boolean), setTopRightCorner(Boolean), setBottomLeftCorner(Boolean), setBottomRightCorner(Boolean)

    • addToGrid

      public boolean addToGrid​(MenuComponent comp, int x, int y)
      This method is overridden and only returns false because PartitionPanel requires components to be added in a very specific way. Each component held must be in the top, bottom, left, or right sector.
      Overrides:
      addToGrid in class Panel
      Parameters:

      whether the addition of the component was successful
      See Also:
      setLeft(MenuComponent), setRight(MenuComponent), setTop(MenuComponent), setBottom(MenuComponent)

    • removeFromGrid

      public boolean removeFromGrid​(int x, int y, boolean resize)
      This method is overridden and returns false because PartitionPanel cannot directly remove a component from the grid. Each component held is in one of four sectors: top, bottom, left, or right.
      Overrides:
      removeFromGrid in class Panel
      Parameters:
      x - the x-value of the component to remove
      y - the y-value of the component to remove
      resize - whether the grid should check for a resize after the deletion.
      Returns:
      whether a component was removed at (x,y)
      See Also:
      setLeft(MenuComponent), setRight(MenuComponent), setTop(MenuComponent), setBottom(MenuComponent)
